@startuml obc_bms_temp_to_cpc_target_soc_thermal_signal_flow
!theme plain
skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam defaultFontSize 11
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam responseMessageBelowArrow true

title OBC BMS Temp To CPC Target SOC Thermal Signal Flow\n(OBC state + BMS thermal context + vehicle state -> CPC thermal state and charge-target SOC)

participant "OBC state bus" as OBC #F4F7FB
participant "BAT_BMS state bus" as BMS #E8F0FE
participant "Vehicle state bus" as Veh #FCE8FF
participant "CPC\ncharge-port owner" as CPC #E8F7E8
participant "Charge-port state bus" as CpcBus #FFF4CC
participant "Observers /\ncharge readers" as Obs #FFF4CC

== CPC Inputs ==

OBC -> CPC : frmObcStateMsg\nObcState / AcPlugState
BMS -> CPC : frmBatBmsStateMsg\nBmsState / PackSoc / PackTemp
Veh -> CPC : frmVehicleStateCanMsg\ngDriveState
activate CPC
CPC -> CPC : obc/bms/vehicle freshness lease checks
CPC -> CPC : if OBC stale then\nobcState = 0 / acPlugState = 0
CPC -> CPC : if BMS stale then\nbmsState = 7 / packSoc = 50 / packTemp = 28
CPC -> CPC : chargeEnable =\n(obcState == 2 and bmsState <= 2 and driveState == 0)
CPC -> CPC : thermalState =\npackTemp >= 45 ? 2 : packTemp >= 35 ? 1 : 0
CPC -> CPC : chargeTargetSoc =\n80 when thermalState == 2,\n90 when packSoc >= 90,\n70 when bmsState >= 3
note right of CPC
Representative gating inputs
- ObcState / AcPlugState
- BmsState / PackSoc / PackTemp
- gDriveState
end note

== CPC Publish ==

CPC -> CpcBus : frmChargePortCtrlStateMsg\nPortLockState / PlugState / ChargeEnable /\nThermalState / ChargeTargetSoc
note right of CPC
Representative outputs
- ChargeEnable
- ThermalState
- ChargeTargetSoc
- PortLockState
end note

== Downstream Visibility ==

CpcBus -> Obs : charge-port visibility /\ncharging observers
deactivate CPC

note over OBC, Obs
Representative runtime chain
1. OBC, BMS, and vehicle state reach CPC
2. CPC evaluates charge-enable posture and thermal condition
3. CPC derives target SOC under thermal and pack-state constraints
4. CPC publishes charge-port control and target-SOC state
end note

@enduml
